        <briefdescription>
<para>This function validates the IV parameters for the specified AES engine mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>EngineMode</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>AES engine mode. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>IvAddr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Address of buffer holding IV. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>IvLen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Length of the IV in bytes.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if IV parameters are validated successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if IV parameters validation fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>IV Validation for respective AES engine modes AES Standard mode (ECB, CBC, CTR, CFB, OFB). AES MAC mode (GCM, CCM, GMAC, CMAC).</para><para><table rows="5" cols="3"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Engine Mode </para></entry><entry thead="yes"><para>IvAddress </para></entry><entry thead="yes"><para>IvLength  </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>AES-ECB, AES-CMAC </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>AES-GCM </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Non-zero </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Any non-zero Length </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>AES-CCM </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Non-zero </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>7 to 13 bytes </para></entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Remaining modes </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>Non-zero </para></entry><entry thead="no"><para>12 or 16 Bytes </para></entry></row>
</table>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
